Happy Friday everyone!  

 I'm doing a little survey, a bit of research you could say.  I have been
all over the country, but I have only had the pleasure of driving a bus on
the east coast, and the west.  Mass, and Cal. to be exact.  In California, I
had a 67 deluxe, and I had a 71 westie.  Driving a vintage VW is a lot more
common out there.  Very rarely was I ever pulled over by police, in fact,
never. And I lived out there for a while.  When I grew up, I lived in Mass,
and it seemed that just being in a VW bus put you at risk of being pulled
over, and hassled.  And a deadhead sticker on it, then you are really asking
for trouble!!!
I'm wondering if it is a problem everyone faces, or does it vary state, to
state?  If the bus is mint, is it different?  Answers, comments, and stories
appreciated!!  :)  
                                      Bus Gypsy

